15#ifndef ISC_STDIO_H
16#define ISC_STDIO_H 1
17
18/*! \file isc/stdio.h */
19
20/*%
21 * These functions are wrappers around the corresponding stdio functions.
22 *
23 * They return a detailed error code in the form of an an isc_result_t. ANSI C
24 * does not guarantee that stdio functions set errno, hence these functions
25 * must use platform dependent methods (e.g., the POSIX errno) to construct the
26 * error code.
27 */
28
29#include <stdio.h>
30
31#include <isc/lang.h>
32#include <isc/result.h>
33
34ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
35
36/*% Open */
37isc_result_t
38isc_stdio_open(const char *filename, const char *mode, FILE **fp);
39
40/*% Close */
41isc_result_t
42isc_stdio_close(FILE *f);
43
44/*% Seek */
45isc_result_t
46isc_stdio_seek(FILE *f, off_t offset, int whence);
47
48/*% Tell */
49isc_result_t
50isc_stdio_tell(FILE *f, off_t *offsetp);
51
52/*% Read */
53isc_result_t
54isc_stdio_read(void *ptr, size_t size, size_t nmemb, FILE *f,
55 size_t *nret);
56
57/*% Write */
58isc_result_t
59isc_stdio_write(const void *ptr, size_t size, size_t nmemb, FILE *f,
60 size_t *nret);
61
62/*% Flush */
63isc_result_t
64isc_stdio_flush(FILE *f);
65
66isc_result_t
67isc_stdio_sync(FILE *f);
68/*%<
69 * Invoke fsync() on the file descriptor underlying an stdio stream, or an
70 * equivalent system-dependent operation. Note that this function has no
71 * direct counterpart in the stdio library.
72 */
73
74ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
75
76#endif /* ISC_STDIO_H */
77
